Well, if you nuke it to death, the mob will die and your pet will live. So that solves that, right? Not quite <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Another factor is aggro. If you're back there blasting away, most mobs will not like it very much and start beating you. This is very bad for mages, as we have NO means of crowd control save our pets. No root, no fear, no mez, and no stun. Just good old Zoner <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
Usuing the earth pet can negate the aggro factor, but the earth root is not the most reliable (personal opinion...errr so is everything else in this, I guess, lol). So, I would say that a combination of heal and nuking is best, although the previous poster was correct in that you will want to stop this at 39, when pet regen goes into high gear, so to speak.<br>
It does depend on the pet, by the way. For the earth pet, you can nuke more (Has more hps and roots to negate aggro). With the fire pet, you will want to heal more (less hp and the damage shield makes up for lack of nukes)<br>
